   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Darong Granulated Calcium Cyanamide</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project will finance:1) an expansion of the calcium cyanamide production from 50,000 tons per annum(tpa) to 150,000 tpa  ;   and 2) the environmental upgrades of 3 existing calcium carbide furnaces, in oder to reduce air emissions and to recover waste heat to generate steam needed for the expansion.    IFC&apos;&apos;s investment will help Darong increase economies of scale and further strengthen its position as a low-cost producer of specialized calcium cyanamide, and its derivative products, in both domestic and International markets. IFC&apos;&apos;s investment will: promote local private sector development; improve living strandards in Northwest China; and will help alleviate proverty in this remote and less developed region.  Through the increased production of the company, the project will provide employment opportunities at a time when local state-owned enterprises are laying off workers.</narrative>
  </description>
